[{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"How to Install Under Cabinet Lighting in Your Kitchen","description":" Add undercabinet lighting to existing kitchen cabinets. This unique method of wiring undercabinet lights eliminates disruptive wall tear-out and minimizes the difficult job of fishing cables from your attic or basement.","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_040-1200.jpg","height":1200,"width":1200},"supply":[{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"1-1/8\" spade bit"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"1/2\" metal flex cable 14/2 plastic-sheathed cable"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"1/2\" spade bit"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Cable clamps"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Fish tape"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"flex connectors"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"junction box"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"remodeling switch box"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"undercabinet lights"},{"@type":"HowToSupply","name":"Wire nuts"}],"tool":[{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Cordless drill"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Hacksaw"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Jigsaw"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Non-contact voltage tester"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Voltage tester"},{"@type":"HowToTool","name":"Wire stripper/cutter"}],"step":[{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step1","name":"Locate a Power Source","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nFind a nearby outlet in the wall opposite the back side of the cabinets and plug in a radio (right). Find the circuit by turning off circuit breakers until the radio goes off.\r\nDetail\r\n\r\n\r\nPlug a radio in to the outlet, then listen for it cutting off when you test the breakers.\r\n\r\n"},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_004-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step2","name":"Open the Wall","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDrill starter holes and cut a 12-in. hole in the back of the cabinet to gain easy access to the outlet (power source). Keep the cut shallow to avoid nicking wires. If you're looking to revamp your cabinets with paint, check out the best paint for kitchen cabinets."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_006-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step3","name":"Add the Initial Junction Box","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAttach flex connectors to a junction box according to your plan (Figure A) and screw it to the back of the cabinet. Align the connectors so the screws point out.\r\nDetail\r\n\r\n\r\nAttach a flex connector for each run of flex wire."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_007-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step4","name":"Drill Holes for Horizontal Runs","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDrill 1-1/8 in. holes in the cabinet sides and feed flex from the metal junction box to each switch and light location."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_009-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step5","name":"Cut the Flex","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMark the flex and cut it off with a hacksaw to the desired length. Build a cutting guide as shown."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_010-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step6","name":"Run Power into the Junction Box","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nRun a cable from the outlet (power source) to the junction box, stripping 12 in. of sheathing off each end. Staple it within 8 in. of the box."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_013-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step7","name":"Fish the Cable","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPull cables through the flex. Use a fish tape for long runs. Leave plenty of cable for running up the walls to the light fixtures."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_014-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step8","name":"Pull the Wire Up to the Wall Cabinet","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDrill a 1/2-in. hole under the wall cabinet and push in the fish tape. Drill a 1-1/8 in. hole through the base cabinet and wall and push in a wire coat hanger to catch the fish tape. Pull the fish tape down, attach the cable and pull it up."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_093-1200.jpg","height":"1500","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step9","name":"Wire the Fixture","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSecure the cable to the fixture with a cable clamp. Connect the wires according to the manufacturer's instructions."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_021-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step10","name":"Attach the Fixture to the Cabinet","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nScrew the fixture to the cabinet bottom and fasten the cable to the cabinet with a standard staple and No. 4 sheet metal screws."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_022-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step11","name":"Cut the Hole for the Switch","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMark the switch box profile on the backsplash. Drill a series of holes with a glass bit and chip out the tile and wallboard.\r\nDetail\r\n\r\n\r\nDrill through tile with a glass bit"},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_017-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step12","name":"Mount the box","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPush the cable into a remodeling box and mount it in the wall."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_018-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step13","name":"Wire the Dimmer","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nConnect the dimmer or switch according to the manufacturer's instructions. Fold the wires into the box and fasten the dimmer and cover plate."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_019-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}},{"@type":"HowToStep","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/#step14","name":"Finish the Wiring","itemListElement":{"@type":"HowToDirection","text":"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nConnect the new wires to the existing wires in the outlet box, black to black (hot), white to white (neutral) and the bare ground wires. Reinstall the outlet."},"Image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_023-1200.jpg","height":"1200","width":"1200"}}]},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"How to Install Under Cabinet Lighting in Your Kitchen","mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/"},"description":"Add dramatic under cabinet lighting in a weekend without tearing up your walls to install the wiring.","datePublished":"2019-07-19T09:00:30Z","dateModified":"2019-09-11T10:34:12Z","author":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman"}],"image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/FH03OCT_03103_040-1200.jpg","height":1200,"width":1200},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/amp_sd_logo.png","width":198,"height":60}},"url":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/how-to-install-under-cabinet-lighting-in-your-kitchen/","dateCreated":"2019-07-19T09:00:30Z","articleSection":"DIY Kitchen Cabinets","creator":[{"@type":"Organization","name":"The Family Handyman"}],"keywords":""},{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/","name":"Home"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/","name":"Kitchen"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@id":"https://www.familyhandyman.com/kitchen/diy-kitchen-cabinets/","name":"DIY Kitchen Cabinets"}}]}]
